  "text": "We focus on the SINR gains for users in the CRE area. By varying the number of macro BSs applying ABSs for the small cell users, we can see the evolution of the maximum CIO above which there is a SINR degradation at the edge of the small cells. The macros considered for muting are the most interfering ones. [CITATION_1] , namely that muting more macro BSs allows us to further increase the CIO. We can also see that the SINR gain obtained by muting more and more macro BSs eventually saturates. Hence an optimal number of macro BSs applying ABS can be found while keeping complexity low.",
